We've got an awesome update for you!

- You now have two buttons below every Tell and are able to easily answer and share every Tell!
- If you open a notification about a new answer, you can now directly navigate to the authors profile
- If you write a message and close the window, the message gets locally saved so you don't have to write it again
- iOS 11 support
- Minor bug fixes

If you experience any issues, just write an email to support@tellonym.me and tell us about!
Thank You & Have Fun with Tellonym!

This is the biggest update yet - and it's pretty cool!

- we added an all-new feed where all your friend's posts are listed - you won't miss anything
- this is such an awesome feature, it deserves two lines
- you are now able to only allow Tells from registered users (everything will still be anonymous)
- fixed a bug with push notification duplicates

Enjoy the new stuff! :)

Annoyed by certain topics in your Tells?
With the all new word filter you're now able to ban specific topics from your inbox.

Getting spammed with Tells about your Cat? Add 'cat' to the new word filter and you won't receive any Tells which contain the word.
Hope you love it!

From now on you can see who likes your answers. You're the sender of a Tell? No problem! You will be shown as "sender" on your Likes and remain anonymous unless you remove the sender status.

With this update, we'll also suggest friends you can follow on Tellonym. It's best to link your contact book.

- we made it easier for new users to find their friends
